data.enText: at a time in the future; after the time you are talking about
See you later.
I met her again three years later.

data.chText: 那年晚些时候他的父亲去世了。
data.enText: His father died later that year.

data.chText: 我们年内晚些时候要到罗马去。
data.enText: We're going to Rome later in the year.

a way of saying goodbye, used by young people
Later, guys!
later on
at a time in the future; after the time you are talking about
I'm going out later on.

data.chText: 过了好长时间，她才明白他的意思。
data.enText: Much later on, she realized what he had meant.
not/no later than…
by a particular time and not after it

coming after sth else or at a time in the future

data.chText: 在后面的一章中对这一点作了更详细的讨论。
data.enText: This is discussed in more detail in a later chapter.

data.chText: 比赛已被推迟到以后的某个日期举行。
data.enText: The match has been postponed to a later date.
near the end of a period of time, life, etc.

She found happiness in her later years.
sooner or later

Sooner or later you will have to make a decision.

ex.chText: 老人星期天病倒了，3天后就离开了人世。
ex.enText: The old man fell ill on Sunday and died three days later.

ex.chText: 她开会迟到了一个钟头。
ex.enText: She came to the meeting an hour later.

ex.chText: 好久以后他才告诉我这件事。
ex.enText: He told me about it long afterwards.

synonyms.bx: 指在已提及的某事件或时间点之后，一般不和具体时间段连用。

tr: happening at a time subsequent to a reference time
example: he's going to the store but he'll be back here later

tr: at some eventual time in the future

example: he stayed later than you did

value.def: You use later to refer to a time or situation that is after the one that you have been talking about or after the present one.

example.ex: Burke later admitted he had lied.
example.tran: 伯克后来承认自己撒了谎。

defx.def: You use later on to refer to a time or situation that is after the one that you have been talking about or after the present one.

example.ex: Later on I'll be speaking to Patty Davis...
example.tran: 等会儿我会跟帕蒂·戴维斯谈。

example.ex: This is only going to cause me more problems later on.
example.tran: 这只会在以后给我带来更多麻烦。

gramarinfo.label: ADV with cl, oft amount ADV

value.def: You use later to refer to an event, period of time, or other thing which comes after the one that you have been talking about or after the present one.

example.ex: At a later news conference, he said differences should not be dramatized...
example.tran: 在后来的新闻发布会上，他说不应夸大分歧。

example.ex: The competition should have been rescheduled for a later date...
A later report said the oil fire on the sea was out.
example.tran: 随后的报道称，海上的石油大火已经熄灭。

value.def: You use later to refer to the last part of someone's life or career or the last part of a period of history.

example.ex: He found happiness in later life...
In his later years he wrote very little...
Her later career was best known for her partnership with Rudolf Nureyev.
example.tran: 在她职业生涯后期，最为人熟知的是和鲁道夫·努列耶夫的搭档组合。

value.boxu_tran: after，afterwards和later均用于指说话时间之后或某事之后发生的事情。later可用于指说话当时之后的时间或情况：I'll go and see her later（我晚些时候会去看她）。a little，much和not much也可与later连用，例如，A little later, the lights went out（片刻后，灯灭了），I learned all this much later（很久以后我才得知这一切）。after可与not long和shortly等连用，例如，After dinner she spoke to him（晚饭后她跟他谈了话），I returned to England after visiting India（印度之行结束后我返回英格兰），Shortly after, she called me（过后不久，她便给我打了电话）。无须提及具体时间或事件时可用afterwards：Afterwards we went to a night club（后来我们去了一家夜总会）。afterwards也可与soon，shortly等连用，例如，Soon afterwards, he came to the clinic（不久之后，他来到诊所）。after，afterwards或later均可用于表示一段时间的短语之后，以说明某事发生的时间。例如，five years after his death（他死后5年），She wrote about it six years afterwards（6年后她撰文提及此事），Ten minutes later he left the house（10分钟后他离开了屋子）。
value.boxu_usage: You use after, afterwards, and later to talk about things that happen following the time when you are speaking, or following a particular event. You can use later to refer to a time or situation that follows the time when you are speaking. I'll go and see her later. 'A little', 'much', and 'not much' can also be used with later. A little later, the lights went out... I learned all this much later. Expressions such as 'not long' and 'shortly' can also be used with after. After dinner she spoke to him... I returned to England after visiting India... Shortly after, she called me. Afterwards can be used when you do not need to mention the particular time or event. Afterwards we went to a night club. You can also use words such as 'soon' and 'shortly' with afterwards. Soon afterwards, he came to the clinic. You can use after, afterwards, or later following a phrase that mentions a period of time, in order to say when something happens. ...five years after his death... She wrote about it six years afterwards... Ten minutes later he left the house.
